text: The dismal swamp chorus frog or Brimley's chorus frog (Pseudacris brimleyi) is a frog. It lives in the east coast of the United States, from Virginia to Georgia. The adult male frog can be 30 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog can be 35 mm long. The skin on the frog's back is light brown with lines in the middle and sides and a dark stripe from the eye to where the legs meet the body. There is a light colored line from the mouth to the ear. The skin of the belly is yellow-white in color. ==References== Category:Frogs of North America
title: Brimley's chorus frog
